<subSubSection id="3BA2CBE1B6AD0033E2DEB2FFF831263D" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="19C49CE601F75B1A297C689C334B92C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC5EA731BE4045B9F2DDBA7F4BA89F2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Iberian Peninsula and northern Africa, distributed in France, Spain, Portugal, and Morocco. Found in Mediterranean, Iberian-Atlantic and cold temperate, often high-elevation, environments of the Pyrenees. Forms part of pioneer grassland species assemblages which grow on very shallow and sandy 
<normalizedToken id="4455E2E78208EF778CD4802B6205A99E" originalValue="‘skeleton’">'skeleton'</normalizedToken>
soils, apparently reliant on climatic humidity in addition to precipitation for its water supply. Usually flowering from June to July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F0B3B426E070B40FE2BDFB40D6E22CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="notes">
<paragraph id="248B20C61CA875CA57312C3100090D9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3F81FA11D2068ADF2A0CAE3295D69FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="FF515C7A5E9068CA988E171E29CFA5D8" authority="P.M.Peterson, K.Romaschenko, R.J.Soreng &amp; S.P.Sylvester, 2020" authorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Soreng &amp; Sylvester" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Soreng &amp; Sylvester" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostula truncatula" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="138226F36A0D44294A4A8C2532D9D2E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostula truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs in its leaf blade anatomy from most other species of 
<taxonomicName id="B72CDB4EDDAF36D73DEB877FDA035ADC" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFBFA0592F89D24A5A93C9FAE9942A06" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having pillars of sclerenchyma which are continuous between the adaxial and abaxial surface of the blades. These continuous pillars of sclerenchyma are exceptionally thick and found only on the margins and central vein in subsp. truncatula, while subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="ACB4F5384E39C238743C2A821EFD27D4" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. durieui" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="truncatula" subSpecies="durieui">durieui</taxonomicName>
has thinner continuous sclerenchyma packets in the margins, central and primary veins (
<bibRefCitation id="65B299A37B8073B05213F2F82EF6C6F2" author="Romero Garcia, AT" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B29" refString="Romero Garcia, AT, Blanca Lopez, G, 1988. Contribucion al estudio cariosistematico del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la Peninsula Iberica. Boletim da Sociedade Broteriana, ser. 2.61: 81-104." title="Contribucion al estudio cariosistematico del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la Peninsula Iberica. Boletim da Sociedade Broteriana, ser. 2.61: 81 - 104." year="1988">
Romero 
<normalizedToken id="1C6DFE46BE17C67B6C7ADC06CD0FBCA9" originalValue="García">Garcia</normalizedToken>
and Blanca 
<normalizedToken id="C06E6A8B0FBADC3BFF635608A0FC4A79" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4C-F). Costal cells and intercostal long cells of the abaxial blade surface are also distinct, with 
<taxonomicName id="FF63D6873121BEDE3F77A8CE6A8CA209" genus="A." lsidName="A. truncatula" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="truncatula">
<emphasis id="262FFBC6DE7C9F4463466566AAAFFEAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. truncatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing from species of 
<taxonomicName id="95411120D44C07172AE0B6971A14CBA0" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D83FDAECA41507697DF1D14504B376FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Iberian Peninsula in having paired s0-z cells in the costal zone, and l3 type long cells in the intercostal zone (
<bibRefCitation id="874CFECB3BE94CDB701469CFF8294E07" author="Romero Garcia, AT" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B29" refString="Romero Garcia, AT, Blanca Lopez, G, 1988. Contribucion al estudio cariosistematico del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la Peninsula Iberica. Boletim da Sociedade Broteriana, ser. 2.61: 81-104." title="Contribucion al estudio cariosistematico del genero Agrostis L. (Poaceae) en la Peninsula Iberica. Boletim da Sociedade Broteriana, ser. 2.61: 81 - 104." year="1988">
Romero 
<normalizedToken id="2AB0B0D371877B04BDA982F4A0E831C0" originalValue="García">Garcia</normalizedToken>
and Blanca 
<normalizedToken id="DB18EE1A873353F1204BF58F398328B4" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
). Stomata are also apparently absent on the abaxial blade surface, a character found in only a few other species in the Iberian Peninsula, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="B54C54EC207CEA733080EC05C272E8B6" authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1844" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis reuteri" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reuteri">
<emphasis id="CF7FD96792E76D0769FA5D6AFA371120" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Agrostis reuteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="643C2E54716CC47FA04C30C702A6B574" authority="P.M.Peterson, K.Romaschenko, R.J.Soreng &amp; S.P.Sylvester, 2020" authorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Soreng &amp; Sylvester" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="P. M. Peterson, Romasch., Soreng &amp; Sylvester" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Alpagrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alpagrostis setacea" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setacea">
<emphasis id="AC888BF7EE669487D81A2BB7B300F784" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Alpagrostis setacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Romero 
<normalizedToken id="7F24A5832E75056B4F8FCB3C86B8AA3F" originalValue="García">Garcia</normalizedToken>
&amp; Blanca 
<normalizedToken id="4089728696ECF176486E927BEC2F9AB7" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
, 1988).
</paragraph>
